WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:03.703
Evan, I know you're nervous

00:03.737 --> 00:05.239
about your first
grown-up haircut,

00:05.273 --> 00:06.707
but you're in safe hands
with Reuben.

00:06.740 --> 00:08.007
He's the best in the biz.

00:08.042 --> 00:09.510
I used to cut
Gregory Hines' hair.

00:11.245 --> 00:12.413
Mm-hmm.
Hmm.

00:12.446 --> 00:13.747
So what will it be today, Louis?

00:13.781 --> 00:15.883
Well, with Chinese New Year
coming up,

00:15.916 --> 00:17.818
we're gonna need extra
fresh cuts.

00:17.851 --> 00:20.821
Better make it two usuals.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.823
Actually, I'll have
the "Randy."

00:22.856 --> 00:23.757
The who?

00:23.791 --> 00:25.659
Randy from "Home Improvement."

00:25.693 --> 00:27.861
You know,
Jonathan Taylor Thomas.

00:27.895 --> 00:29.397
Is that one person
or three people?

00:29.430 --> 00:31.699
One, but with the talent
of three.

00:31.732 --> 00:33.834
Okay, your haircut,
your choice.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.070
One usual
and one "Randy," please.

00:36.104 --> 00:38.005
A usual and a "Randy,"
coming up.

00:38.038 --> 00:40.741
I hope we don't run into
any balloons on our way home

00:40.774 --> 00:43.477
because we are
gonna look sharp.

00:46.547 --> 00:48.349
[ Chuckling ]
Thanks, Reuben.

00:48.382 --> 00:50.918
See, what did I tell you?
Isn't Reuben the best?

00:57.491 --> 00:59.593
-- Captions by VITAC --

00:59.627 --> 01:00.794
* Fresh off the boat

01:00.828 --> 01:02.530
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:02.563 --> 01:04.632
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

01:04.665 --> 01:05.966
* Fresh off the boat

01:05.999 --> 01:08.402
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

01:08.436 --> 01:09.737
* But I know where I'm goin'

01:09.770 --> 01:12.806
* I'm fresh off the boat

01:12.840 --> 01:14.975
[ Birds chirping ]

01:17.411 --> 01:20.881
Art thou the bird
who man loves best?

01:20.914 --> 01:24.752
The pious bird
with the scarlet breast.

01:24.785 --> 01:28.456
Is that a "Yes, I returned
Marvin's birdfeeder"

01:28.489 --> 01:30.791
or a "No, I didn't return
Marvin's birdfeeder"?

01:30.824 --> 01:31.725
Yes, I returned it.

01:31.759 --> 01:33.093
Good, Louis is clean.

01:33.127 --> 01:35.296
That just leave you boys,
with the exception of Emery,

01:35.329 --> 01:36.930
who is clean all year round.

01:36.964 --> 01:37.898
I don't get why
we're going through

01:37.931 --> 01:39.600
all this trouble
for a holiday.

01:39.633 --> 01:41.402
Having a clean slate is
an important part

01:41.435 --> 01:42.970
of the lunar New Year.

01:43.003 --> 01:45.639
All debts, disputes, and grudges
have to be resolved

01:45.673 --> 01:48.309
in order to ensure good fortune
for the coming year.

01:48.342 --> 01:50.411
Mom's just looking out
for future us.

01:50.444 --> 01:52.980
Well, she better also be
looking out for Mariah Carey

01:53.013 --> 01:54.815
because that's who
future me is married to.

01:54.848 --> 01:56.417
I'm gonna marry Jewel.

01:56.450 --> 01:58.652
[ Sternly ]
Stay away from Jewel.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.522
Evan, did you settle things
with Carol-Joan

02:01.555 --> 02:03.090
after your incident?

02:03.123 --> 02:06.126
And so the bartender says,
"Why the big pause?"

02:06.160 --> 02:07.528
And the bear says --

02:07.561 --> 02:09.197
"I don't know.
I've always had them."

02:09.229 --> 02:11.199
[ Laughter ]

02:22.210 --> 02:24.478
I apologized
with a fig basket.

02:24.512 --> 02:26.146
It's done.
Good.

02:26.180 --> 02:27.715
Eddie, did you care
for Grandma's flowers

02:27.748 --> 02:29.149
like I asked you to?

02:29.183 --> 02:30.184
Care for them?

02:30.218 --> 02:31.385
I spoiled them.

02:31.419 --> 02:33.521
Turns out,
they love Mr. Pibb.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.359
Technically, it's still alive,
so good enough.

02:41.429 --> 02:43.197
Second cousin Susan?

02:43.231 --> 02:44.932
You've been in a fight with her
for 30 years.

02:48.736 --> 02:50.704
Louis, do you know
what this means?

02:50.738 --> 02:53.241
This could be the first time
our entire family has

02:53.274 --> 02:55.409
a clean slate
for the New Year!

02:55.443 --> 02:58.145
Imagine what that kind
of good fortune could mean

02:58.178 --> 03:00.514
for our future business dealings
and scratch-offs.

03:00.548 --> 03:02.583
But, Mom, you've never had
a clean slate.

03:02.616 --> 03:04.918
You always end up getting
into a fight with somebody.

03:04.952 --> 03:06.654
You're kind of
a loose cannon.

03:06.687 --> 03:08.689
A loose cannon
downs more ships.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.724
I don't --
Don't worry.

03:10.758 --> 03:12.360
This year,
to ensure success,

03:12.393 --> 03:14.728
I am putting myself
on lock down.

03:14.762 --> 03:18.098
If I don't leave the house,
I can't get into any fights.

03:18.131 --> 03:19.767
Really? You're just
gonna stay inside?

03:19.800 --> 03:21.201
I've already run
all my errands,

03:21.235 --> 03:23.337
paid all my debts,
settled my disputes,

03:23.371 --> 03:25.806
and had enough time
to rent "Courage Under Fire."

03:41.154 --> 03:42.456
Um...

03:42.490 --> 03:43.491
Who is that?

03:55.068 --> 03:56.737
Very.

04:06.079 --> 04:07.481
[ Sighs ]

04:11.251 --> 04:13.554
Simon, welcome.

04:13.587 --> 04:14.822
Eddie will take
good care of you.

04:14.855 --> 04:16.923
[ Whispering ]
Me? Have Evan do it.

04:16.957 --> 04:19.327
He's basically a big Evan.
Look at him!

04:19.360 --> 04:22.496
Welcoming family is an important
New Year's tradition.

04:22.530 --> 04:24.465
He is your new
"Grandma's flowers."

04:24.498 --> 04:26.166
Don't let him die.

04:27.668 --> 04:30.638
[ Tune of "Hit Me
with Your Best Shot" ]
* Organize my dress socks

04:30.671 --> 04:34.408
* Why don't I organize
my dress socks? *

04:34.442 --> 04:39.413
* Organize my dress socks
and put them away *

04:39.447 --> 04:40.848
Uh...Dad.

04:40.881 --> 04:43.584
Oh, Evan, hi. What's up?

04:43.617 --> 04:45.419
I have a problem.

04:45.453 --> 04:48.288
The letter was right here,
stamped and addressed,

04:48.322 --> 04:49.457
and now it's gone.

04:49.490 --> 04:51.492
So? Your mom
probably mailed it.

04:51.525 --> 04:54.261
You don't understand.
The letter was hate mail.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.029
You sent hate mail?

04:56.063 --> 04:58.198
I was gonna send it
 after the New Year,

04:58.231 --> 05:00.000
but then someone went
and mailed it.

05:00.033 --> 05:01.935
Now Reuben's gonna
read it today,

05:01.969 --> 05:04.204
and I'll have bad luck
for the entire year.

05:04.237 --> 05:05.373
Evan, relax.

05:05.406 --> 05:06.940
I'm sure whoever...

05:06.974 --> 05:08.342
Wait.

05:08.376 --> 05:09.510
Reuben who?

05:09.543 --> 05:11.044
You know, Reuben.

05:11.078 --> 05:12.012
Your barber?

05:14.815 --> 05:16.216
* [ Rapping ] Your rhymes
are like air balls *

05:16.249 --> 05:17.651
* Mine are Magic, I Shaq it

05:17.685 --> 05:19.019
* You tryin' to kill me
in a battle? *

05:19.052 --> 05:20.654
* Break out that old
Browns jacket *

05:20.688 --> 05:21.989
Ooh!

05:22.022 --> 05:23.190
Ooh!
Ooh!

05:23.223 --> 05:25.559
Eddie!
Trent:
I hate the Browns now.

05:25.593 --> 05:26.694
What are you doing?

05:26.727 --> 05:28.328
Get in here and take care
of your cousin.

05:28.362 --> 05:30.731
I found him reading
an old MAD magazine.

05:30.764 --> 05:32.733
I was teaching him
about America through humor.

05:32.766 --> 05:34.067
"Dunces with Wolves."

05:34.101 --> 05:35.936
[ Laughs ] Genius.

05:38.939 --> 05:40.374
That's your cousin?

05:40.408 --> 05:41.375
Is he cool?

05:41.409 --> 05:44.244
His shorts
almost touch his nipples.

05:48.516 --> 05:50.751
What if he reads your letter
and won't cut my hair anymore?

05:50.784 --> 05:53.086
Or he tells the other barbers?
You know how they talk.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.655
Do you know how hard it is
to find a good barber?

05:54.688 --> 05:56.323
It's like dating
but for your hair.

05:56.356 --> 05:57.725
He's not that good, Dad.

05:57.758 --> 05:59.527
I mean, look at this mess.

05:59.560 --> 06:02.530
I asked for a "Randy,"
and he gave me a "Brad."

06:02.563 --> 06:04.598
Nobody knows
who those people are!

06:04.632 --> 06:07.234
I've been going to Reuben
since we moved to Orlando.

06:07.267 --> 06:09.169
I can't start over
and find somebody new.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.838
Maybe he won't
know who sent it.

06:10.871 --> 06:12.773
I signed the letter...
"Unhappy Customer."

06:12.806 --> 06:15.008
Oh, really? [ Chuckles ]

06:15.042 --> 06:17.177
What else did it say?

06:17.210 --> 06:19.847
It said, "You don't know
how to cut Asian hair.

06:19.880 --> 06:21.949
I asked for a 'Randy,'
and you gave me a 'Brad.'"

06:21.982 --> 06:23.784
Evan, he's gonna know
that's us!

06:23.817 --> 06:24.952
Put your shoes on.

06:24.985 --> 06:26.219
We've got to
get that letter back

06:26.253 --> 06:28.121
before it ruins the New Year
for the both of us.

06:28.155 --> 06:29.156
[ Sighs ]

06:30.123 --> 06:34.227
[ Movie plays on TV ]

06:34.261 --> 06:36.096
Ugh!

06:36.129 --> 06:38.766
Well, good thing
I'm wearing my movie jeans

06:38.799 --> 06:41.068
and not my lucky red --

06:41.101 --> 06:42.302
[ Gasps ]

06:42.335 --> 06:43.904
Emery...[ Sighs ]

06:43.937 --> 06:45.973
I need your help.
What's up?

06:46.006 --> 06:48.576
I forgot to pick up my lucky red
dress from the dry cleaner's --

06:48.609 --> 06:51.278
the one I've worn every
New Year's since I retired

06:51.311 --> 06:54.214
my women's-powersuit-
dragon-broach combo in 1989.

06:54.247 --> 06:55.949
And, let me guess, you want me
to make you a new one.

06:55.983 --> 06:57.485
What? No.

06:57.518 --> 06:59.787
No, I want you to come
to the dry cleaner's with me

06:59.820 --> 07:01.755
to pick it up.
Why me?

07:01.789 --> 07:02.956
Because I want to make it

07:02.990 --> 07:04.224
to New Year's dinner
with a clean slate,

07:04.257 --> 07:06.226
and I don't trust myself
out there alone.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.962
So you want me
to be your kindness Sherpa,

07:08.996 --> 07:11.064
your karma spirit guide,
your bodyguard for --

07:11.098 --> 07:13.066
Enough examples, but yes.

07:13.100 --> 07:14.602
You get along
with everybody,

07:14.635 --> 07:17.805
so I'm just
gonna follow your lead.

07:17.838 --> 07:19.907
No more loose cannon.

07:19.940 --> 07:21.308
Don't worry, Mom.

07:21.341 --> 07:22.743
Just put your hand
on my shoulder,

07:22.776 --> 07:25.579
and I'll guide you,
like a seeing eye dog except --

07:25.613 --> 07:26.714
I'll wait outside.

07:33.854 --> 07:38.759
[ Wind chimes ring loudly ]

07:38.792 --> 07:40.828
Hey! You like?

07:40.861 --> 07:43.263
We brought it back
from New Mexico.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.465
Too big for the overhead,
so we had to check them.

07:45.499 --> 07:47.267
If the wind blows
just right,

07:47.300 --> 07:49.369
they play the intro
to "Jack & Diane."

07:49.402 --> 07:50.504
[ Laughs ]

07:50.538 --> 07:52.105
Emery, go get
my step ladder

07:52.139 --> 07:54.642
and the big scissors
I use to cut meat.

07:54.675 --> 07:56.276
We love them!

07:56.309 --> 07:58.111
Wind chimes are
nature's instrument.

07:58.145 --> 08:00.180
[ Both chuckle ]

08:00.213 --> 08:01.281
What are you doing?

08:01.314 --> 08:02.716
Those pipes sound
like somebody

08:02.750 --> 08:04.985
let an octopus loose
in the Williams-Sonoma.

08:05.018 --> 08:07.354
I know, Mom, but if you're
gonna stay clean today,

08:07.387 --> 08:09.056
you're gonna need
to control your temper.

08:09.089 --> 08:10.891
I'm your kindness Sherpa,
remember?

08:10.924 --> 08:12.660
Yes, you're right.

08:12.693 --> 08:15.195
But just so you know,
as soon as the New Year is over,

08:15.228 --> 08:16.630
I'm going to steal
those chimes

08:16.664 --> 08:18.666
and drop them
in the bottom of the ocean.

08:18.699 --> 08:20.133
I know you will, Mom.

08:20.167 --> 08:22.703
Hide them where no one
can find them.
Okay, Mom.

08:22.736 --> 08:25.338
Wrap them in chains,
drive them to the pier,

08:25.372 --> 08:26.640
and then I'm gonna
drop them off --

08:26.674 --> 08:29.509
Mom! I get it.
You hate the chimes.

08:30.944 --> 08:33.746
Ding-dong! You're
at the bottom of the ocean.

08:33.780 --> 08:36.249
[ Video game music plays ]

08:36.283 --> 08:37.918
Are you sure
I'm controlling the Koopas?

08:37.951 --> 08:40.220
Yeah, yeah, I told you,
I control Mario,

08:40.253 --> 08:41.889
and you control
the Koopas and the Boos.

08:41.922 --> 08:42.956
It's how the game works.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.193
Hey, what'd you
do that for?

08:53.366 --> 08:55.402
Grandma, what does it look
like I'm doing?

08:55.435 --> 08:56.269
He's having fun.

09:02.743 --> 09:04.912
Grandma, that's
a great idea.

09:04.945 --> 09:07.114
I know just the place.

09:07.147 --> 09:08.248
Hey, Simon.

09:08.281 --> 09:09.249
Have you ever...

09:09.282 --> 09:11.551
built a bear?

09:11.585 --> 09:14.221
I built a miniature model
of the Titanic once

09:14.254 --> 09:15.422
for history class.

09:15.455 --> 09:16.590
I used Tic Tacs
for the life boats.

09:16.624 --> 09:18.125
Uh-huh.

09:18.158 --> 09:19.727
Well, here,
you build a bear.

09:19.760 --> 09:21.094
All the cool kids do it.

09:21.128 --> 09:23.096
Okay, do you want
to build one together?

09:23.130 --> 09:24.965
We can make it a blend
of both of us.

09:24.998 --> 09:27.534
What boy names do you like?
I like Carl.

09:27.567 --> 09:30.203
It's kind of something
you do by yourself.

09:30.237 --> 09:32.906
Like, the bear chooses you.
That kind of thing.

09:32.940 --> 09:34.507
Have fun.

09:40.180 --> 09:42.883
And then you just hand the
dry cleaner your ticket, smile,

09:42.916 --> 09:44.084
and I'll handle the rest.

09:44.117 --> 09:45.919
He calls me "Jessie."

09:45.953 --> 09:48.088
You know that? Jessie.

09:48.121 --> 09:49.790
Like I'm
a German shepherd.

09:49.823 --> 09:51.825
You can do this.
I believe in you.

09:51.859 --> 09:54.594
All we have to do
is walk over there and --

09:54.628 --> 09:56.429
Uh-oh.

09:56.463 --> 09:59.332
Hello, can you spare any change
today to save the whales?

10:00.333 --> 10:02.402
Okay, new plan.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.504
I go in alone
and get your dress.

10:04.537 --> 10:06.807
What do I do?
You stay here, relax,

10:06.840 --> 10:09.042
and listen to
the soothing sounds of NPR.

10:10.610 --> 10:13.513
Man: And with that,
 Coney Island was born.

10:13.546 --> 10:15.649
The boardwalk,
 the cotton candy,

10:15.683 --> 10:17.685
and, of course,
 La Marcus Thompson's

10:17.718 --> 10:19.252
[ Yawns ]
 switchback gravity railway.

10:19.286 --> 10:20.921
You know what?

10:20.954 --> 10:22.756
I am relaxed.

10:22.790 --> 10:24.692
I'll be back
in five minutes.
Okay.

10:24.725 --> 10:26.827
Stay in the car
and lock the doors.
Mm.

10:26.860 --> 10:28.195
The island itself?

10:28.228 --> 10:30.363
Named for all the Coneys,
 or rabbits...

10:33.500 --> 10:35.368
Louis: Reuben always
goes on break at 1:30.

10:35.402 --> 10:36.937
He'll head to the back
to eat a yogurt,

10:36.970 --> 10:38.939
and we can duck in and see if
the letter's been delivered yet.

10:38.972 --> 10:40.307
How will we know?

10:40.340 --> 10:41.341
Reuben always gets
a new issue

10:41.374 --> 10:42.976
of Sports Illustrated
in the mail.

10:43.010 --> 10:44.177
If the new issue's
on the counter,

10:44.211 --> 10:45.312
that means the mail
has been delivered,

10:45.345 --> 10:46.446
and it's too late.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.048
If it's still last week's,
we're okay.

10:51.318 --> 10:52.319
Now's our chance.
Let's go.

10:57.424 --> 10:59.392
"America's Top 50 Jock Schools."

10:59.426 --> 11:00.627
Is that this week's
or last week's?

11:00.660 --> 11:02.229
I only read "Zillions."

11:02.262 --> 11:04.564
Last week's, which means
the mail hasn't been --
[ Door opens ]

11:04.597 --> 11:07.000
Louis.

11:07.034 --> 11:08.969
What are you doing here?

11:09.002 --> 11:10.804
Oh. [ Laughs ]

11:10.838 --> 11:15.208
We're here because, um,
Evan needs another haircut.

11:18.912 --> 11:21.581
Thanks, Reuben,
great work as always.

11:21.614 --> 11:23.917
This is great. Reuben hasn't
gotten your letter yet.

11:23.951 --> 11:25.753
Great? Look at my hair.

11:25.786 --> 11:27.721
I look like Grace Jones.

11:27.755 --> 11:30.758
What's the problem?
She's a handsome woman.

11:30.791 --> 11:32.659
* [ Rapping ] You don't
want this fire *

11:32.692 --> 11:34.227
* My words burn,
bet your health *

11:34.261 --> 11:35.495
* Put you out with water

11:35.528 --> 11:36.529
* But you're only gonna
wet yourself *

11:36.563 --> 11:38.365
Hey, cousin Eddie.

11:38.398 --> 11:40.533
You were right about that place.
It was awesome.

11:40.567 --> 11:42.002
You can design your bear's
shirt and everything.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.737
I made one of you...

11:43.771 --> 11:45.372
and one of me.

11:45.405 --> 11:47.107
Why is mine holding
a fishing rod?

11:47.140 --> 11:48.341
I had to guess
your hobbies.

11:48.375 --> 11:50.677
Nice tweddy bear, Eddie.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.913
Walter, give me a beat.

11:52.946 --> 11:54.381
[ Beatboxing ]

11:54.414 --> 11:55.415
* [ Rapping ] I don't
know you, dawg *

11:55.448 --> 11:56.884
* If we're related,
it's barely *

11:56.917 --> 11:58.051
* I could care less

11:58.085 --> 11:59.853
* So if I'm hating,
it's barely *

11:59.887 --> 12:01.054
* Why are you here,
ringside? *

12:01.088 --> 12:02.622
* You made weight?
Barely *

12:02.655 --> 12:05.292
* Oh, you're just watching,
on a date with bear me *

12:05.325 --> 12:07.294
* Come to my town,
and you're whacker than whack *

12:07.327 --> 12:09.797
* Pick any store, Simon,
I'll get a bag for you to pack *

12:09.830 --> 12:12.199
* Return to manufacturer,
It's personality you lack *

12:12.232 --> 12:14.567
* I'm done babysitting,
I'll just give my money back *

12:14.601 --> 12:15.602
Oh!Oh!

12:15.635 --> 12:16.703
Oh!Oh!

12:16.736 --> 12:21.074
Ohhhhhhh!

12:28.916 --> 12:30.583
* [ Rapping ] Young Frankenstein
thinks I'm dumb? *

12:30.617 --> 12:32.485
* Well, the truth is,
I'm dumb nice *

12:32.519 --> 12:33.987
* You's a sucker
like a lollipop *

12:34.021 --> 12:35.889
* In other words,
you're dumb twice *

12:35.923 --> 12:37.124
* You think
you're better, wrong *

12:37.157 --> 12:38.225
* You think
you're fresher, wrong *

12:38.258 --> 12:39.326
* And after this spanking

12:39.359 --> 12:40.393
* I'mma call you
Wedgie Huang *

12:40.427 --> 12:41.594
* An hour away from you?

12:41.628 --> 12:43.163
* I was thrilled,
on balance *

12:43.196 --> 12:45.165
* Yeah, I built two bears
I charged it to your allowance *

12:45.198 --> 12:47.300
* So call your mom
to pick us up *

12:47.334 --> 12:49.469
* Then do us a favor --
shut your trap *

12:49.502 --> 12:52.439
* I'm in Orlando to see Mickey,
not a little Goofy rap *

12:52.472 --> 12:53.841
-That was so cool.
-That was tight.

12:53.874 --> 12:54.908
[ Laughter ]

12:54.942 --> 12:57.177
-How did you do that?
-Sick, man.

12:57.210 --> 12:58.278
-That was so cool.
-Love it.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.349
Woman: And that's where
 I met my husband,

13:02.382 --> 13:04.684
right there on the boardwalk.
Why is this taking so long?

13:04.717 --> 13:06.820
He was an engineer
 on the Cyclone,

13:06.854 --> 13:08.856
and I sold cotton candy
 at the --

13:12.392 --> 13:14.461
**

13:18.899 --> 13:20.500
Hello.

13:20.533 --> 13:22.302
Can you spare any change today
to save the whales?

13:24.804 --> 13:25.839
Yes.

13:29.676 --> 13:31.378
[ Coins clink ]

13:32.846 --> 13:33.881
You owe me another $5.

13:33.914 --> 13:35.648
I gave a $20.

13:35.682 --> 13:37.050
No, you gave me a $10.

13:37.084 --> 13:38.518
You owe me another $5.

13:38.551 --> 13:40.653
Oh, now you're
in for it, buddy.

13:40.687 --> 13:42.022
Mom, this guy's a liar,

13:42.055 --> 13:43.256
and he's trying
to steal my money.

13:46.026 --> 13:48.561
Emery, just pay the man
what he says you owe him.

13:48.595 --> 13:49.796
What?

13:49.829 --> 13:51.131
Me?

13:51.164 --> 13:52.499
But he's a liar.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.868
You come into my store
and call me a liar?

13:54.902 --> 13:56.369
That's it.

13:56.403 --> 13:58.471
You're going on the wall.

13:58.505 --> 13:59.572
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

14:04.511 --> 14:06.013
Aren't you gonna
say anything?

14:07.347 --> 14:08.615
[ Sighs ]

14:10.783 --> 14:14.754
Great, now how are people going
to know we do shoes?

14:22.029 --> 14:24.331
Why didn't you stick up for me?
Don't you believe me?

14:24.364 --> 14:26.166
Of course, I believe you.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.400
We're supposed to be
avoiding conflicts,

14:27.434 --> 14:28.768
not starting new ones.

14:28.801 --> 14:30.070
Last week, you yelled
at a bus driver

14:30.103 --> 14:31.571
for not wearing his hat.

14:31.604 --> 14:33.907
But the one time I need you
to get angry for me,

14:33.941 --> 14:35.208
you leave me hanging?

14:35.242 --> 14:37.244
You care more about
your holiday superstitions

14:37.277 --> 14:38.378
than you do about me.

14:38.411 --> 14:40.213
No. That is not true.

14:40.247 --> 14:42.916
I just want our whole family

14:42.950 --> 14:46.053
to start out the New Year
on the right foot for once.

14:46.086 --> 14:48.621
That is worth $5 to me.

14:48.655 --> 14:51.724
So please, just go in there
and give that man his money.

14:51.758 --> 14:53.426
No way.

14:55.762 --> 14:59.399
You know, $5 could
de-barnacle a whole pod.

15:01.001 --> 15:02.769
Okay, now let's go over
the plan again.

15:02.802 --> 15:05.072
I pretend to lose my car keys
down this grate,

15:05.105 --> 15:06.940
then when the mailman
comes to help me,

15:06.974 --> 15:08.741
I hit the mail out
of his hands,

15:08.775 --> 15:10.377
you grab the letter
and rip it up.

15:10.410 --> 15:11.644
Isn't holding up a mailman

15:11.678 --> 15:13.580
worse than just
sending an angry letter?

15:13.613 --> 15:15.248
Can we just
ask for it back?

15:15.282 --> 15:17.417
Have you ever tried reasoning
with a mailman, son?

15:17.450 --> 15:19.619
You can't. They're crazy.
You've got to come strong.

15:19.652 --> 15:21.955
Oh. [ Laughs ]
Thank God you're here.

15:21.989 --> 15:24.257
Uh, my keys have
fallen down this grate.

15:24.291 --> 15:25.758
Oh, no.
Yeah.

15:25.792 --> 15:26.926
Now!

15:26.960 --> 15:28.495
What'd you do that for?

15:28.528 --> 15:30.730
Oh, uh, I'm sorry.
I don't know what came over --

15:30.763 --> 15:31.631
Now!

15:31.664 --> 15:32.499
Will you stop doing that?

15:32.532 --> 15:33.967
[ Siren wails ]

15:34.001 --> 15:35.335
Everything okay, Louis?

15:35.368 --> 15:37.637
Looks like you're trying
to assault a federal employee.

15:37.670 --> 15:38.905
Assault? [ Laughs ]

15:38.938 --> 15:40.340
Oh, no.

15:40.373 --> 15:43.243
I just, uh -- I --
my keys fell down a grate.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.911
Look, I'm late
for a bat mitzvah,

15:44.944 --> 15:46.279
so I'm gonna let you off
with a warning.

15:46.313 --> 15:49.482
Just, you know, be cool.

15:51.351 --> 15:53.753
[ Whistling ]

15:53.786 --> 15:55.955
There goes my relationship
with Reuben.

15:55.989 --> 15:57.624
[ Sighs ] We didn't get
the letter back,

15:57.657 --> 15:59.326
and I have
a terrible haircut.

15:59.359 --> 16:01.628
My year of bad luck has
already begun.

16:06.333 --> 16:09.302
So you didn't exactly get
the haircut you wanted.

16:09.336 --> 16:11.638
I didn't like my haircut
when I first went to Reuben.

16:11.671 --> 16:13.940
I wanted the "Clooney,"
but he gave me this.

16:13.973 --> 16:15.808
After a while,
I got used to it.

16:15.842 --> 16:18.278
Why'd you keep going back to him
if it wasn't what you wanted?

16:18.311 --> 16:21.181
I don't know.
He was just so nice.

16:21.214 --> 16:23.116
He called me "Big Guy."

16:23.150 --> 16:24.484
I didn't want
to hurt his feelings.

16:24.517 --> 16:26.453
Plus, it's a good haircut.

16:26.486 --> 16:28.288
But it could be
a great haircut.

16:28.321 --> 16:31.991
You said that finding the
right barber was like dating.

16:32.025 --> 16:34.894
Would you have settled
for anyone less than Mom?

16:34.927 --> 16:36.796
No.

16:36.829 --> 16:37.997
You deserve
the "Clooney," Dad.

16:38.031 --> 16:38.865
We all do.

16:50.110 --> 16:53.846
[ Wind chimes ring
to the tune of "Jack & Diane" ]

16:55.282 --> 16:57.016
Looks like
we're getting a storm.

16:57.050 --> 16:58.685
[ Laughs ]

17:05.925 --> 17:07.827
That's right, girls.

17:07.859 --> 17:09.462
Sing for your supper.

17:11.431 --> 17:13.566
Are you sure? I could have
sworn I gave you a $20.

17:13.599 --> 17:16.002
Nope. You gave me a $10.
I'm sure of it.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.704
You owe me another $5.

17:23.242 --> 17:24.911
[ Sighs ] Not you again.

17:24.944 --> 17:28.681
I am here to make
things right for my son.

17:28.715 --> 17:31.618
This is the extra $5
he owes you.

17:31.651 --> 17:33.286
I apologize
for his behavior.

17:33.320 --> 17:35.922
And I ask that you take his
photo down from your shame wall

17:35.955 --> 17:39.092
so he can start out the New Year
with a clean slate.

17:39.126 --> 17:40.727
Apology accepted.

17:40.760 --> 17:43.230
But only because
I need the business.

17:43.263 --> 17:46.566
My wife has...
expensive tastes.

17:49.436 --> 17:51.604
My son's photo, please.
Oh!

17:56.776 --> 17:58.978
Thank you.

17:59.011 --> 18:01.314
And now you're going to want
to take my picture.

18:01.348 --> 18:02.749
Why would I want to take --
Trust me.

18:02.782 --> 18:05.652
You're going to want
to take my picture.

18:06.619 --> 18:08.588
**

18:10.923 --> 18:13.460
Hey.
Hey.

18:13.493 --> 18:14.894
What you did back there --

18:14.927 --> 18:16.229
It -- [ Sighs ]
It was impolite.

18:16.263 --> 18:17.930
I'm sorry.

18:17.964 --> 18:20.066
Don't be sorry.
You were awesome.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.501
I'm the one who should be
saying sorry

18:21.534 --> 18:22.669
for the way I treated you.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.237
You're not mad
that I embarrassed you?

18:24.271 --> 18:26.273
I was just mad
because you were so good.

18:26.306 --> 18:29.342
I mean, you rhymed "balance"
with "allowance."

18:29.376 --> 18:30.743
You're amazing, dawg.

18:30.777 --> 18:32.412
How'd you get so dope
at freestyling?

18:32.445 --> 18:33.680
I love hip-hop.

18:33.713 --> 18:35.348
How come you never
said anything?

18:35.382 --> 18:36.849
You never asked.

18:36.883 --> 18:38.185
Hmm.

18:38.218 --> 18:39.286
For real though,

18:39.319 --> 18:41.288
you could become
a famous rapper one day.

18:41.321 --> 18:42.855
Rap's just a hobby for me.

18:42.889 --> 18:44.324
My real passion is
marine biology.

18:44.357 --> 18:46.926
Do you see any
Asian rappers in here?

18:46.959 --> 18:47.827
Me neither.

18:47.860 --> 18:49.095
You have a gift.

18:49.128 --> 18:51.030
You have a chance
to change the game.

18:51.063 --> 18:53.032
I'll think about it.

18:53.065 --> 18:54.301
Come on.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.278
How did you get this?

19:05.312 --> 19:07.113
I'm sorry for
not having your back.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.615
I get it.

19:08.648 --> 19:10.783
It's Chinese New Year,
and you wanted to start clean.

19:10.817 --> 19:12.952
It's not just that.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.487
I didn't stand up for you

19:14.521 --> 19:17.390
because I don't want to set
that kind of example for you.

19:17.424 --> 19:18.691
I don't want to teach you
that fighting

19:18.725 --> 19:19.826
is always the answer.

19:19.859 --> 19:22.395
But you fight
with, like, everybody --

19:22.429 --> 19:24.697
delivery guys, firemen,

19:24.731 --> 19:26.566
the cat outside
the frozen yogurt place.

19:26.599 --> 19:27.734
Yes.

19:27.767 --> 19:29.168
And you're good.

19:29.202 --> 19:31.003
And you get along
with everybody.

19:31.037 --> 19:33.206
And you're always smiling.

19:33.240 --> 19:34.707
I don't want you
to be more like me.

19:34.741 --> 19:36.243
I want to be
more like you.

19:37.877 --> 19:39.746
I've witnessed
the softening

19:39.779 --> 19:42.749
of the hardest of hearts
by a simple smile.

19:42.782 --> 19:43.850
Goldie Hawn said that.

19:47.720 --> 19:49.322
Goldie...

19:49.356 --> 19:51.123
also sounds like
a dog's name.

20:01.368 --> 20:02.635
[ Speaking Chinese ]

20:05.638 --> 20:07.340
What happened to your hair?

20:07.374 --> 20:08.541
Tried out a new barber.

20:08.575 --> 20:10.243
He finally gave me
exactly what I asked for --

20:10.277 --> 20:11.344
the "Clooney."

20:11.378 --> 20:12.178
You hate it, don't you?

20:12.211 --> 20:13.713
So much.

20:13.746 --> 20:15.248
[ Inhales deeply ]
But at least now I know.

20:15.282 --> 20:18.050
Like I know sending that letter
won't bring me bad luck

20:18.084 --> 20:21.220
because it wasn't hate mail,
it was truth mail.

20:21.254 --> 20:22.355
[ Chuckles ]

20:22.389 --> 20:24.291
You did it, Mom.

20:24.324 --> 20:26.125
You made it to the New Year
with a clean slate.

20:26.158 --> 20:28.828
Yeah...

20:39.406 --> 20:41.140
Uh, orange and full of juice.

20:41.173 --> 20:43.242
Um...an orange?

20:43.276 --> 20:44.243
The color of my first car.

20:44.277 --> 20:45.312
Tan!

20:45.345 --> 20:46.446
Powder blue!

20:46.479 --> 20:47.747
Electric plum!

20:47.780 --> 20:49.882
You're shouting
in my ear.

20:49.916 --> 20:51.651
It's tangerines.

20:51.684 --> 20:55.254
Now sit back and enjoy
the entertainment.

20:55.288 --> 20:56.723
* [ Rapping ] Big ups
to the Huangs *

20:56.756 --> 20:58.124
* Never say you ain't
the flyest *
Never!

20:58.157 --> 20:59.626
* You can't pick
your own family *

20:59.659 --> 21:01.728
* but you can
pick your hair stylist *
Uh-huh!

21:01.761 --> 21:04.397
* My man Louis the wildest,
Jessica mad stylish *
Yo!

21:04.431 --> 21:06.899
* Evan's on a short leash,
and Emery the least childish *
Uh-huh.

21:06.933 --> 21:09.902
* Mario to my Luigi,
Eddie my partner in rhyme *

21:09.936 --> 21:11.304
* Any problems with my people

21:11.338 --> 21:13.005
* We'll silence you
like the chimes *
Bing-bang.

21:13.039 --> 21:14.407
* All love, same blood

21:14.441 --> 21:15.808
* From the womb to the tomb

21:15.842 --> 21:17.344
* Just don't ask me to leave

21:17.377 --> 21:18.611
* I already took Evan's room

21:18.645 --> 21:19.512
Sorry, Evan!

21:19.546 --> 21:21.314
[ Laughter, cheering ]

21:21.348 --> 21:22.949
Well, that's great.

21:25.452 --> 21:26.886
Who is that?
